HEADWORD: Armhole
<hw>Arm"hole`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Arm</ets> +
<ets>hole</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The cavity under the shoulder;
the armpit.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A hole for the arm in a garment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Armiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
